  "prompt": "When I record my face and the video I am reacting to on the same computer, the audio plays in the background of webcam footage. How do I fix it?",
  "response": "To prevent the audio from the reaction video from playing in the background of your webcam footage, try these solutions:\n\n1. Use external audio output\n- Use headphones or external speakers\n- This separates the audio from your recording\n\n2. Screen recording software options\n- OBS Studio: Allows separate audio track selection\n- Streamlabs: Has audio mixing features\n- Camtasia: Offers audio control settings\n\n3. Audio settings in recording software\n- Mute system audio during recording\n- Use \"Desktop Audio\" or \"System Audio\" toggle\n- Adjust audio input/output devices\n\n4. Computer sound settings\n- Disable audio output for the specific application\n- Use Windows sound mixer to control app volumes\n- On Mac, use Audio MIDI Setup\n\n5. Alternative recording methods\n- Record reaction video and screen separately\n- Use two different devices\n- Edit audio tracks later in video editing software\n\nThe best solution depends on your specific software and setup. Try these methods to find what works for you.",
